To remove ambiguity on the format of the date string in the solution proposed by @aochsner  would it not be better to define this constructor instead?
public IgnoreAttribute(string reason, int year, int month, int day, int hour=0, int minute=0, int second=0)
{
year = year % 9999;
month = month % 12;
day = day % numDaysInMonth;
hour = hour % 24;
minute = minute % 60;
second = second % 60;
//Generate a DateTime from the specified values
this.upTo = new DateTime(year, month, day, hour, minute, second);
}

I'd rather use a named parameter for this, instead of creating a new
constructor.

Charlie

